  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of emergency shelter and NFI assistance to vulnerable households affected by floods</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to restore safe housing conditions to reduce both loss of life and life-threatening risks to the most vulnerable and economically disadvantaged households. This $1,000,000 UNDP Project is providing cash grants for home repairs, procuring and delivering gender-responsive household items, supporting the technical design of disaster-resilient repair and conducting rapid trainings for households, local masons and construction workers on resilient repair techniques, among other activities. The project provides life-saving assistance to 26,582 people, including 9,914 women, 9,757 men, 3,428 boys, 3,438 girls and 1,052 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
